# Performance Optimization

## React.memo
- Use `React.memo` for components that:
  - Render frequently
  - Receive stable props
  - Are expensive to render
- Always set `displayName` for memoized components

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
const ProjectCard = React.memo<ProjectCardProps>(({ title }) => {
  return <div>{title}</div>
})

ProjectCard.displayName = 'ProjectCard'
export { ProjectCard }
```

## useCallback and useMemo
- Use `useCallback` for functions passed as props to memoized components
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations
- Don't overuse - profile first

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  handleTabChange(index)
}, [index, handleTabChange])

// ❌ Incorrect (if not needed)
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  handleTabChange(index)
}, [index, handleTabChange]) // when component is not memoized
```

## Code Splitting
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components when appropriate
- Leverage Next.js automatic code splitting

## Optimization Best Practices
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use stable references for callbacks and objects
- Profile before optimizing
